::: {.intro-content .slide-in}
# My name is Benjamin Tjepkes and this is *meum portfolium*.

Experienced in ecology, delving into geography, and actively practicing geospatial -- my passion lies in the realm of applied science.

:::
:::


::: {.about}

::: {.consultant-info}


::: {.index-section-heading}
## Biography {.index-h2}


::: {.index-h2-line}
:::
:::

#### Dedicated to applied science. {.index-h4}

:::{.index-list}

I am a **wildlife ecologist** and **geospatial practitioner** interested in advancing the science behind natural resource conservation. My work focuses on using a variety of data science and geospatial tools to research and inform the natural world. I have over 7 years of progressive experience in the **conservation and environmental science** sector. I am currently pursuing my **Masters in Geography** at the University of Missouri. Updates on my thesis work are coming soon! Please [reach out](contact.qmd) if you have any inquires or would like to collaborate on any ecological or geospatial projects.

:::

::: {#site-listings}

:::

:::

:::




::: {.content-block}


::: {.index-section-heading}
## Proficiencies {.index-h2}

::: {.index-h2-line}
:::
:::

#### Dedicated to lifelong learning. {.index-h4}

:::{.index-list}

Whether in a professional setting, during my academic pursuits, or through personal exploration, I consistently engage in a process of ongoing learning. I have actively pursued various independent educational modules aimed at **enhancing my proficiency** in the geospatial, ecological, and analytical sciences. See how I use these skills [here](gallery.qmd) or read about them [here](posts.qmd).

:::

::: {.features}

::: {.feature}
### {{< fa square-check size=1x >}} GIS & Cartography
Adept as using open source and proprietary software to create static and dynamic map products.

::: {.learn-more}
**Skills:** *R/RStudio, ArcGIS Pro/Online, QGIS*
:::
:::

::: {.feature}
### {{< fa square-check size=0.5x >}} Data Visualization
Proficient in data visualization and reproducible reporting for technical and creative projects.

::: {.learn-more}
**Skills:** *Quarto, R/Rmd, Jupyter Notebooks*
:::
:::

::: {.feature}
### {{< fa square-check size=0.5x >}} Research Methods
Knowledge of the scientific method, research project development, and technical reporting.

::: {.learn-more}
**Skills:** *Mendeley, Zotero, OSF*
:::
:::

::: {.feature}
### {{< fa square-check size=0.5x >}} Web Development
Employ front-end web development techniques to design functional and beautiful websites.

::: {.learn-more}
**Skills:** *HTML, CSS, WordPress, Git/GitHub*
:::
:::

::: {.feature}
### {{< fa square-check size=0.5x >}} Applied Ecology
Experience using radio telemetry, standardized field sampling, and wildlife capture/marking techniques.

::: {.learn-more}
**Skills:** *Field Surveys, Species Monitoring*
:::
:::

::: {.feature}
### {{< fa square-check size=0.5x >}} Data Management
Use programs like Microsoft Access to maintain high-quality data in relational databases.

::: {.learn-more}
**Skills:** *Microsoft Access, SQL Server, Excel*
:::
:::


:::
:::


::: {.bg-banner-3}

::: {.index-section-heading}
## Designs {.index-h2}

::: {.index-h2-line}
:::
:::

#### Dedicated to technical creativity. {.index-h4}


:::{.index-list}

My professional work often involves deep dives into data and data wrangling, so I try to make some fun visuals? Most of my creative workflows involve time in ArcGIS Pro, R/RStudio, QGIS, or Python/Jupyter Notebooks. When I have time, I like to participate in social media challenges, like MapPromptMonday and TidyTuesday. Find the entirety of my gallery [here](gallery.qmd).

:::

